1. Non-Commercial Use
---------------------
You may use, study, and reproduce the Work for:
- academic research
- non-commercial educational use
- internal organizational evaluation
- local, private experimentation

A short attribution is required for derivative explanations:
"Based on StarPolaris OS / Hoshimiya Script (Hoshimiya Ω)."

2. Commercial Use (Prohibited without Permission)
-------------------------------------------------
The following require explicit written authorization from Hoshimiya:
- commercial use of the Work (direct or indirect revenue)
- large-scale model training
- integration into products, services, consulting, or workflows
- redistributing this architecture
- using the Work as the basis for a public or monetized system

3. Derivative OS Frameworks (Prohibited)
----------------------------------------
Publicly publishing derivative works—forks, renamed variants,
approximations, or frameworks substantially copying the architecture—
is prohibited without written authorization.

Private/local experimentation is allowed.

4. Prompt Resale & Template Commercialization (Prohibited)
-----------------------------------------------------------
You may not sell:
- prompt sets derived from the Work
- “AI OS templates” based on the Work
- simulations of the architecture as commercial services

5. AI Model Simulation Clause
-----------------------------
AI models (Grok / Gemini / ChatGPT / Perplexity etc.) may simulate or
emulate the structure **for research or learning**.

However, commercial packaging, resale, or redistribution of such
simulations as standalone frameworks is prohibited.

6. Redistribution / Modification
--------------------------------
You may not redistribute, modify, or publicly publish any portion of the
Work, unless explicitly permitted in writing by Hoshimiya.

7. Authorized Derivatives — Exception
-------------------------------------
A derivative work may be published if ALL of the following are met:
1. Submitted to Hoshimiya for review;
2. Structural and philosophical compatibility confirmed;
3. Written authorization issued.

8. No Misrepresentation
------------------------
You must not claim authorship of the Work, imply official endorsement,
or obscure its origin.

9. No Warranty
--------------
The Work is provided “as is,” without warranty of any kind.
Use at your own risk.

